Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.60,0:01:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Jinn] Locked away\Nby her cruel father,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.35,0:01:50.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Salem was a girl who\Ndesired but one thing:
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.52,0:01:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,freedom.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.39,0:01:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,She lived in a time
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.52,0:01:58.35,Default,,0,0,0,,when kings and their\Nkingdoms were plentiful,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.35,0:02:01.39,Default,,0,0,0,,when men and women were\Ncapable of greatness,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.39,0:02:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and magic was a gift from the\Ngods that all could wield.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.98,0:02:09.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet, there she sat within her tower.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.60,0:02:17.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Until one day, a legendary hero\Ncame to brave the challenges
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.48,0:02:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,within the tower's walls.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.93,0:02:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The people of the lands knew him...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.98,0:02:23.98,Default,,0,0,0,,as Ozma.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.56,0:02:28.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Unlike those who had come before,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.68,0:02:30.35,Default,,0,0,0,,this warrior was not driven
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.35,0:02:33.31,Default,,0,0,0,,by the prize of the young maiden's hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.31,0:02:35.85,Default,,0,0,0,,He fought only for righteousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.85,0:02:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And his pure heart and\Ncourageous soul prevailed.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.18,0:02:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,They escaped the wretched fortress,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.85,0:02:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and yet, something bound them together.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.56,0:03:00.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Ozma had been ready to\Ngive his life for justice
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.18,0:03:04.93,Default,,0,0,0,,countless times but now saw\Na woman worth saving it for.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.02,0:03:09.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And Salem, to her\Nsurprise, found her freedom
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.48,0:03:12.23,Default,,0,0,0,,not in the outside world\Nshe had yearned for
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.23,0:03:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,but in the eyes of the\Nman that had saved her.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.85,0:03:17.85,Default,,0,0,0,,- So where should we go now?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.14,0:03:20.97,Default,,0,0,0,,- Wherever you'd like.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.98,0:03:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Jinn] The two fell deeply in love,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.35,0:03:26.02,Default,,0,0,0,,planned adventures around the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.02,0:03:27.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and lived happily ever after.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.77,0:03:33.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Or at least that's what should have been.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.89,0:03:39.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Ozma, the infallible\Nhero of legend, fell ill.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.85,0:03:42.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And where all of the beasts\Nand blades of the world
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.93,0:03:46.68,Default,,0,0,0,,had fallen short, a\Nsingle sickness prevailed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.68,0:03:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,(Salem sobs)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.43,0:03:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,- How could the gods let this happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.18,0:03:59.10,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Jinn] The gods,\Nbrothers of light and darkness,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.10,0:04:01.64,Default,,0,0,0,,creation and destruction.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.64,0:04:04.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Salem prayed they would see the injustice
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.02,0:04:07.27,Default,,0,0,0,,that had befallen her love\Nand make things right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.18,0:04:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The Domain of Light was a sacred place.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.39,0:04:20.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It was here the elder brother dwelled
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.52,0:04:23.23,Default,,0,0,0,,beside his fountain of life and creation.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.43,0:04:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It was here where mankind\Nwould fall to ruin.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.31,0:04:46.06,Default,,0,0,0,,(dramatic music)
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.98,0:05:00.81,Default,,0,0,0,,- Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.02,0:05:04.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Please bring him back to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.23,0:05:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,- I understand your pain,\Nbut you demand of me
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.10,0:05:10.85,Default,,0,0,0,,that which I cannot make so.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.27,0:05:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Life and death are part\Nof a delicate balance.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.27,0:05:22.35,Default,,0,0,0,,- So you won't do it then?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.23,0:05:25.65,Default,,0,0,0,,- To disrupt the cycle of --
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.64,0:05:28.14,Default,,0,0,0,,- But that's not fair.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.14,0:05:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not fair!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.23,0:05:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,- Let him rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.23,0:05:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,- No.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.10,0:05:52.77,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Jinn] The God of Darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.02,0:06:00.27,Default,,0,0,0,,None dare to enter his home
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.27,0:06:02.81,Default,,0,0,0,,as men knew what monstrosities emerged
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.81,0:06:05.02,Default,,0,0,0,,from his blackened pools of annihilation.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.56,0:06:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And so you must understand\Nthe Dark Lord's surprise
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.93,0:06:13.85,Default,,0,0,0,,when he found a lone\Nwoman kneeling before him.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.48,0:06:19.23,Default,,0,0,0,,(dramatic music)
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.43,0:06:31.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Salem understood it well.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.81,0:06:34.39,Default,,0,0,0,,She told him of the loss and professed
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.39,0:06:38.27,Default,,0,0,0,,that she knew only he\Ncould answer her prayers,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.27,0:06:41.35,Default,,0,0,0,,all while careful to make\Nno mention of his elder.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.93,0:06:43.97,Default,,0,0,0,,- Rise, child.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.18,0:06:47.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And let your faith in me be rewarded.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.77,0:07:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,(Ozma gasps)
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.43,0:07:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,- Where am I?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.73,0:07:05.81,Default,,0,0,0,,What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.81,0:07:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Where am I?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.64,0:07:07.64,Default,,0,0,0,,- It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.64,0:07:09.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything's going to be okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.81,0:07:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,(thunder rumbles)
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.18,0:07:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,- What have you done?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.68,0:07:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,- I have done what I please, brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.23,0:07:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You may bask in the powers of creation,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.43,0:07:24.76,Default,,0,0,0,,but you do not own them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.68,0:07:27.93,Default,,0,0,0,,- This is not creation.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.93,0:07:29.31,Default,,0,0,0,,- Do not lecture me!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.98,0:07:37.77,Default,,0,0,0,,- I will do what I must to maintain order.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.77,0:07:40.52,Default,,0,0,0,,(dramatic music)
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.85,0:07:46.02,Default,,0,0,0,,- No!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.02,0:07:46.85,Default,,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.85,0:07:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,What did you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.68,0:07:49.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Bring him back!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.23,0:07:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,- You dare enter my domain\Nand show such disrespect!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.73,0:07:55.65,Default,,0,0,0,,- Ozma!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.64,0:07:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,- I am abiding by the\Nrules we agreed upon.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.48,0:08:01.94,Default,,0,0,0,,- Rules that I now see\Nare ever in your favor.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.93,0:08:04.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet, the day a mortal\Ncomes to pray at my feet
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.60,0:08:07.31,Default,,0,0,0,,before your own, so do you arrive
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.31,0:08:09.35,Default,,0,0,0,,to lay your judgment upon me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.85,0:08:17.77,Default,,0,0,0,,(explosion blasts)
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.06,0:08:23.69,Default,,0,0,0,,- I know we have our differences,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.68,0:08:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,but I have not come here\Nwith the aim to control you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.48,0:08:31.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The same, however, cannot be said for her.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.23,0:08:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,This woman came to you only\Nafter I denied her pleas,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.43,0:08:37.06,Default,,0,0,0,,pleas that would have\Ndisrupted the balance
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.06,0:08:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,that you and I created.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.31,0:08:40.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Together.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.98,0:08:45.06,Default,,0,0,0,,- Then it seems I owe you an apology.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.06,0:08:47.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Allow me to correct my mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.81,0:08:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,- No!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.43,0:08:57.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.81,0:08:58.89,Default,,0,0,0,,you monsters!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.81,0:09:01.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Give him back to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.39,0:09:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Give him back!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.10,0:09:08.18,Default,,0,0,0,,(God of Light roars)
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.56,0:09:25.69,Default,,0,0,0,,- When you first came\Nto me, I did pity you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.31,0:09:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,But it is clear now
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.31,0:09:31.48,Default,,0,0,0,,that your selfishness and\Narrogance have led you astray.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.35,0:09:35.27,Default,,0,0,0,,- What did you do to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.27,0:09:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,- [God of Light] I have made you immortal.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.02,0:09:39.73,Default,,0,0,0,,- Immortal?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.73,0:09:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,- You cannot die.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.43,0:09:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You cannot be with your beloved.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.27,0:09:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Gods of Light And Darkness]\NSo long as this world turns,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.56,0:09:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,you shall walk its face.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.77,0:09:52.81,Default,,0,0,0,,- [God of Light] You\Nmust learn the importance
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.81,0:09:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,of life and death.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.02,0:09:57.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Only then may you rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.43,0:10:03.93,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Jinn] Salem was\Na prisoner once again.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.93,0:10:06.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Her fruitless attempts\Nto reunite with Ozma
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.68,0:10:08.18,Default,,0,0,0,,eventually became nothing more
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.18,0:10:11.18,Default,,0,0,0,,than acts of spite and\Ndefiance against the gods.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.18,0:10:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,(Salem groans)
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.64,0:10:20.89,Default,,0,0,0,,But perhaps the gods were not\Nas powerful as they seemed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.89,0:10:23.97,Default,,0,0,0,,She had lied to them, turned\Nthem against one another.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.98,0:10:27.81,Default,,0,0,0,,They were fallible.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.81,0:10:31.14,Default,,0,0,0,,If she were to turn humanity\Nagainst light and darkness,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.14,0:10:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,she could rid herself of their\Ncurse.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.85,0:10:35.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Or at the very least...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.23,0:10:37.81,Default,,0,0,0,,she could make them suffer.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.23,0:10:43.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Salem traveled from\None kingdom to another,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.98,0:10:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,telling tales of how she stole\Nimmortality from the gods,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.60,0:10:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,welcomed any swordsman to cut her down,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.14,0:10:52.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and demonstrated her powers.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.52,0:10:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,With the kings and queens in awe,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.39,0:10:57.43,Default,,0,0,0,,she pulled them deeper into her scheme.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.43,0:10:59.31,Default,,0,0,0,,She painted them pictures of a time
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.31,0:11:02.02,Default,,0,0,0,,when they would no longer\Nhave to watch their loved ones
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.02,0:11:04.94,Default,,0,0,0,,wither and die, when they\Ncould claim the powers
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.93,0:11:07.06,Default,,0,0,0,,of their creators for themselves,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.06,0:11:09.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and in turn, perfect their own design.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.77,0:11:12.35,Default,,0,0,0,,(crowd cheers)
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.23,0:11:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,All they needed to do was\Ndestroy their old masters.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.48,0:11:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The gods had hoped that Salem would learn
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.48,0:11:24.86,Default,,0,0,0,,from her eternal curse, and she did.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.77,0:11:29.31,Default,,0,0,0,,She learned that the hearts\Nof men are easily swayed.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.23,0:11:39.61,Default,,0,0,0,,- [God of Light] Who has\Nled you down this path?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.93,0:11:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,- You.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.10,0:11:53.10,Default,,0,0,0,,(suspenseful music)
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.43,0:12:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,My own gift to them...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.23,0:12:04.77,Default,,0,0,0,,used against me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.64,0:12:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,- No.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.23,0:12:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.06,0:12:28.73,Default,,0,0,0,,(Salem grunts)
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.73,0:12:31.61,Default,,0,0,0,,- You thought there was\Nno greater punishment
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.60,0:12:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,we could bestow upon you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.98,0:12:35.15,Default,,0,0,0,,- I'll come back.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.14,0:12:38.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll tell the rest of the\Nworld of this massacre,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.06,0:12:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,build a new army.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.27,0:12:41.73,Default,,0,0,0,,- You do not understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.73,0:12:45.11,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no one left.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.18,0:12:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You are all that remains of humanity.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.48,0:12:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,- This planet was a beautiful experiment,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.39,0:12:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,but it is merely a remnant\Nof what it once was.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.85,0:13:01.77,Default,,0,0,0,,We will learn from this failure.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.73,0:13:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope that you will learn from yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.73,0:13:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,- No, you can't leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.14,0:13:09.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't leave!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.60,0:13:11.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Come back!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.18,0:13:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,- Still demanding things of your creators.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.68,0:13:34.76,Default,,0,0,0,,(explosion blasts)
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.77,0:13:37.94,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Jinn] Once again, Salem was alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.31,0:13:42.94,Default,,0,0,0,,She cursed the gods.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.93,0:13:44.97,Default,,0,0,0,,She cursed the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.98,0:13:48.77,Default,,0,0,0,,She cursed everything,\Neverything but herself.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.81,0:13:51.69,Default,,0,0,0,,She wandered the face of the planet,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.68,0:13:53.85,Default,,0,0,0,,awaiting a death that would never come...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.81,0:13:57.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Until fate led her back\Nto the land of darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.02,0:14:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,This was it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.43,0:14:05.18,Default,,0,0,0,,This had to be it, the brothers\NGrimm, the pools of black
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.18,0:14:08.60,Default,,0,0,0,,that continued to give rise\Nto horrific nightmares.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.60,0:14:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,If the fountain of life\Ngranted her immortality,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.89,0:14:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,then surely, the pools of Grimm\Nwill finally take it away.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.52,0:14:18.44,Default,,0,0,0,,She was wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.73,0:14:23.81,Default,,0,0,0,,This force of pure destruction
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.81,0:14:27.14,Default,,0,0,0,,could not destroy a\Nbeing of infinite life.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.14,0:14:31.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, it created a\Nbeing of infinite life
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.18,0:14:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,with a desire for pure destruction.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.02,0:14:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And in time, she would find her adversary.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.89,0:14:45.64,Default,,0,0,0,,(dramatic music)
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.81,0:15:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,- [God ff Light] Ozma.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.77,0:15:11.81,Default,,0,0,0,,- Where am I?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.93,0:15:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,- We are between realms.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.64,0:15:19.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm afraid a tragedy\Nhas befallen your home
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.18,0:15:20.60,Default,,0,0,0,,at the hands of my brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.73,0:15:25.77,Default,,0,0,0,,We have chosen to depart this\Nworld, but in our absence,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.77,0:15:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I would like to offer you\Nthe chance to return to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.89,0:15:32.39,Default,,0,0,0,,- I don't understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.64,0:15:38.39,Default,,0,0,0,,- Mankind is no more,\Nyet your world remains.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.39,0:15:40.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And in time, your kind will grow
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.39,0:15:42.81,Default,,0,0,0,,to walk its face once again.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.81,0:15:44.73,Default,,0,0,0,,However, without our presence,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.73,0:15:47.27,Default,,0,0,0,,they will be but a fraction\Nof what they once were.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.64,0:15:52.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Creation, destruction,\Nchoice and knowledge
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.89,0:15:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,were the ideals upon\Nwhich humanity was made.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.81,0:15:59.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I leave them behind with the hope
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.93,0:16:02.35,Default,,0,0,0,,that you will learn to remake yourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.23,0:16:07.77,Default,,0,0,0,,If brought together, these four relics
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.77,0:16:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,will summon my brother\Nand I back to your world,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.48,0:16:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and humanity will be judged.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.10,0:16:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,If your kind has learned to\Nlive in harmony with one another
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.18,0:16:21.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and set aside their differences,\Nthen we shall once again
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.68,0:16:25.72,Default,,0,0,0,,live among you, and humanity\Nwill be made whole again.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.10,0:16:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,But if your kind is unchanged,\Nif you demand our blessings
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.64,0:16:33.10,Default,,0,0,0,,while still fighting amongst yourselves,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.10,0:16:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,then man will be found irredeemable
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.68,0:16:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and your world will be\Nwiped from existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.43,0:16:43.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Until your task is complete,\Nyou will reincarnate,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.18,0:16:48.39,Default,,0,0,0,,but in a manner that\Nensures you are never alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.85,0:16:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,- I'm sorry, but that world
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.64,0:16:54.68,Default,,0,0,0,,just isn't as dear to me without her.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.73,0:17:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,If I may, I'd rather return\Nto the afterlife to see Salem.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.43,0:17:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,- [God of Light] You\Nwill not find her there.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.23,0:17:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,- You mean she isn't gone?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.39,0:17:10.52,Default,,0,0,0,,- Salem lives, but the woman you hold dear
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.52,0:17:12.27,Default,,0,0,0,,in your memories is gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.43,0:17:14.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Heed this warning...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.39,0:17:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,where you seek comfort,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.98,0:17:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,you will only find pain.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.48,0:17:22.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So, will you--
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.35,0:17:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,- I'll do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.89,0:17:25.77,Default,,0,0,0,,- Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.93,0:17:29.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Our creation rests within your hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.85,0:17:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Jinn] And so Ozma was reborn.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.98,0:17:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,(crowd screams)
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.60,0:17:50.43,Default,,0,0,0,,- Where am I?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.98,0:17:55.31,Default,,0,0,0,,(man screams)
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.31,0:17:56.14,Default,,0,0,0,,- Help!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.18,0:18:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.27,0:18:10.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, tell me your name.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.14,0:18:11.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.77,0:18:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,- He didn't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.81,0:18:20.10,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Jinn] Ozma had found himself
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.10,0:18:22.98,Default,,0,0,0,,in a world completely unfamiliar to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.98,0:18:24.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Cities looked different.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.64,0:18:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Creatures known as the\NFaunus wore fangs and claws
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.60,0:18:29.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and were locked away in cages.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.85,0:18:32.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And without the blessing of the gods...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.27,0:18:36.77,Default,,0,0,0,,no one could perform magic like\Nmankind was once capable of,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.77,0:18:41.06,Default,,0,0,0,,no one but himself and a\Nwoman known as...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.06,0:18:42.06,Default,,0,0,0,,the witch.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.52,0:18:46.85,Default,,0,0,0,,During his years of travel,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.85,0:18:48.98,Default,,0,0,0,,he heard the same frightened whispers
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.98,0:18:52.86,Default,,0,0,0,,that spoke of a terrifying\Nsorceress who commanded
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.85,0:18:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,,dark powers in the wilds\Namong the beasts and monsters.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.98,0:19:02.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Ozma was convinced that\Nthis witch was Salem...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.27,0:19:05.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and decided he needed to\Nsee what she had become.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.14,0:19:21.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Call it magic or call\Nit something stronger,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.39,0:19:24.43,Default,,0,0,0,,but in that moment, the two knew exactly
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.43,0:19:26.43,Default,,0,0,0,,who it was that stood before them.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.98,0:19:31.77,Default,,0,0,0,,- What do we do now?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.77,0:19:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,- Whatever we like.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.93,0:19:37.43,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Jinn] As Salem and\NOzma recounted the events
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.43,0:19:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,which had brought them back together,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.18,0:19:41.81,Default,,0,0,0,,each withheld parts of their story.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.81,0:19:44.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Salem, fearing Ozma would reject her,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.27,0:19:47.27,Default,,0,0,0,,blamed the end of the world on the gods.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.27,0:19:50.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Ozma, still unsure of where the truth lay,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.64,0:19:53.81,Default,,0,0,0,,kept his task and the relics a secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.81,0:19:58.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Though time passed and all\Nseemed well, Ozma's conversation
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.10,0:20:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,with the God of Light\Nstill lingered in his mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.89,0:20:02.39,Default,,0,0,0,,He had found happiness,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.39,0:20:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,but humanity seemed more\Ndivided than ever before.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.14,0:20:08.93,Default,,0,0,0,,- Are you surprised?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.93,0:20:11.85,Default,,0,0,0,,This world is quite literally godless.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.85,0:20:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,These humans have no one to guide them.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.35,0:20:17.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps that's all they need.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.39,0:20:19.10,Default,,0,0,0,,- What are you saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.31,0:20:23.06,Default,,0,0,0,,- We could become the gods of this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.06,0:20:25.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Our powers surpass all others.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.23,0:20:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Our souls transcend death.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.98,0:20:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,We can mold these lands\Ninto whatever we want,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.52,0:20:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,what you want, create the paradise
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.06,0:20:36.77,Default,,0,0,0,,that the old gods could not.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.10,0:20:40.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The hearts of men...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.68,0:20:43.47,Default,,0,0,0,,are easily swayed.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.48,0:20:46.15,Default,,0,0,0,,(crowd screams)
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.35,0:20:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,(Nevermore growls)
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.60,0:21:19.39,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Jinn] The two amassed a following.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.39,0:21:22.35,Default,,0,0,0,,That following grew into\Na prosperous kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.52,0:21:25.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And at the head of that kingdom blossomed...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.43,0:21:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,a family.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.85,0:21:32.60,Default,,0,0,0,,(dramatic music)
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.31,0:21:52.02,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Ozma] Are we sure this is right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.02,0:21:55.40,Default,,0,0,0,,- You said we needed to\Nbring humanity together.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.39,0:21:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,In order to do that, we\Nhave to spread our word
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.31,0:22:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and destroy those who will deny it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.64,0:22:06.68,Default,,0,0,0,,- What are we doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.10,0:22:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,This isn't what he asked of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.98,0:22:17.31,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Salem] What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.31,0:22:20.23,Default,,0,0,0,,- Mother, father, look!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.43,0:22:25.18,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Jinn] It was a miracle.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.18,0:22:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Their children could perform magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.89,0:22:32.52,Default,,0,0,0,,But what should have been a\Njoyous occasion was short lived.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.06,0:22:38.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Ozma told Salem\Neverything, the true reason
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.52,0:22:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the God of Light had brought him back,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.39,0:22:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the relics that lay\Nscattered around the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.68,0:22:47.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and the day of judgment he\Nhad been told to prepare for.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.23,0:22:49.81,Default,,0,0,0,,- Don't you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.81,0:22:51.56,Default,,0,0,0,,None of that matters anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.52,0:22:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Why spend our lives trying\Nto redeem these humans
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.43,0:22:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,when we can replace them with\Nwhat they could never be?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.64,0:23:11.47,Default,,0,0,0,,- Mommy?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.14,0:23:23.89,Default,,0,0,0,,(dramatic music)
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.77,0:23:44.60,Default,,0,0,0,,(Grimm growl)
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.31,0:24:00.27,Default,,0,0,0,,- We finally had freedom.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.35,0:24:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,- I...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.23,0:24:09.61,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Jinn] Thus began\Na long and painful cycle
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.60,0:24:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,of death and rebirth for Ozma.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.98,0:24:16.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Some lives were spent in mourning.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.31,0:24:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Many were spent attempting\Nto forget it all.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.18,0:24:22.68,Default,,0,0,0,,But no matter what, his mind\Nwould eventually turn back
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.68,0:24:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,to the task he had been burdened with.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.52,0:24:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And as the centuries went on,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.23,0:24:29.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Ozma began to learn the\Nimportance of living
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.81,0:24:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,with the souls with\Nwhich he had been paired.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.35,0:24:35.85,Default,,0,0,0,,But no matter where or how he lived,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.85,0:24:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,her presence was always felt.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.64,0:24:43.14,Default,,0,0,0,,If humanity were ever to stand\Na chance of being united,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.14,0:24:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,one thing was clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.81,0:24:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,- He had to destroy Salem.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.81,0:24:51.31,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Jinn] Knowing he could\Nnever rid the world of her
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.31,0:24:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,through any mortal means,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.18,0:24:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Ozma sought out the power of the relics.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.77,0:24:59.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Armed with my knowledge, he\Nbelieved he could fulfill
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.77,0:25:01.65,Default,,0,0,0,,his promise to the God of Light.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.48,0:25:08.06,Default,,0,0,0,,- Where are the other relics?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.06,0:25:10.31,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Jinn] He asked me his questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.31,0:25:11.98,Default,,0,0,0,,- What powers do they possess?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.98,0:25:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Jinn] And though\NI gave him my answers--
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.02,0:25:15.77,Default,,0,0,0,,- How do I destroy Salem?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.14,0:25:19.85,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Jinn] Not all of them were to his liking.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.85,0:25:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.81,0:25:29.23,Default,,0,0,0,,(wind howls)
